PCs and other mobile devices offer countless benefits to users all over the world, but many devices we use today are still vulnerable to malware and cyber-attacks. This is because many devices are being sold without security safeguards, adequate privacy controls or lifecycle support. In this day and age, managing your devices should be easier. This is why HP’s premium PCs are reinforced with hardened security features, built from the ground up. They deliver world-class integrated security and manageability so businesses can work how they want, where they want and whenever they want. A variety of powerful features ensure that their customers’ data remains secure. The powerful security features built-in include the following: HP’s premium PC range is available with security built in. View the range below. <img class="size-full wp-image-312275 aligncenter" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/HP-PCs-Elite-Family.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/HP-PCs-Elite-Family.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/HP-PCs-Elite-Family-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/HP-PCs-Elite-Family-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> HP’s Elite PC family offers powerful performance and reliable security in and out of the office. The ultra-slim HP EliteBook x360, for example, is powered by an Intel Core i7 processor, which allows you to get work done, take notes and share content confidently – all in the knowledge that you have a multi-layered defence to combat cybercrime. <img class="size-full wp-image-312681 aligncenter" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/HP-Zbook-Studio.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/HP-Zbook-Studio.jpg 640w, http